{"id":477545,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suspicion_(1941_movie)","text":"\"Suspicion\" is a 1941 romantic thriller movie. It is based on the novel Before the Fact. The movie was directed by Alfred Hitchcock. Cary Grant plays Johnnie, a gambler. Joan Fontaine plays Lina. Dame May Whitty plays Martha.\nThis movie was nominated for Academy Awards for the Best Picture and the Best Original Score. Fontaine won the Best Actress award.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Romance_(love)","surface_form":"romantic","offset":22},{"uri":"Thriller_(genre)","surface_form":"thriller","offset":31},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":40},{"uri":"Before_the_Fact","surface_form":"Before the Fact","offset":72},{"uri":"Alfred_Hitchcock","surface_form":"Alfred Hitchcock","offset":115},{"uri":"Cary_Grant","surface_form":"Cary Grant","offset":133},{"uri":"Joan_Fontaine","surface_form":"Joan Fontaine","offset":170},{"uri":"May_Whitty","surface_form":"May Whitty","offset":201},{"uri":"Academy_Award","surface_form":"Academy Award","offset":255},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture","surface_form":"Best Picture","offset":278},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Original_Music_Score","surface_form":"Best Original Score","offset":299},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Actress","surface_form":"Best Actress","offset":337}]}